data.title: Terry Peden - 2010 - Football
data.meta_description: Terry Peden (45) DL  - Hoof Prints: Talented athlete who has continued to get bigger and stronger...has played both defensive end and tackle in his career. Sophomore
data.text:
Hoof Prints: Talented athlete who has continued to get bigger and stronger...has played both defensive end and tackle in his career.

Sophomore (2010): Battled through injuries throughout the season, seeing action in three games... recovered a fumble in a win over Rhode Island (9/2)... had three total tackles against Baylor (9/11)... had a tackle against Temple (10/23).

Redshirt Freshman (2009): Appeared in 11 games...totaled five tackles, two for a loss and a sack on the season...added team-best three quarterback hurries...had a tackle and quarterback hurry against Bowling Green (11/3), Ohio (11/10) and Miami (OH) (11/18)...had his first career sack at Kent State (11/27).

Freshman (2008): Redshirted in his first season at Buffalo.
